What is Java?


Java is a computer programming language that is concurrent, class-based, object-oriented, and specifically designed to have as few implementation dependencies as possible. The principle idea behind Java's design is being able to run on any platform that has the Java Virtual Machine (JVM) installed.


How do I learn Java or any other programming language?


Many people initialy find programming very confusing to learn. The main reason is that when you program, you need to think like a computer. Once you understand the computational thinking that programming intails, it becomes much easier. If you are struggling to learn Java, you could try using 
Scratch
 which lets you learn the most important concepts while not having to worry about the syntax since you just drag and drop blocks.


Once you learn the bascis, make sure to try and work on a simple project (such as a basic calculator, number guessing game, or rock paper scissors) in order to reinforce concepts. A great place to go if you are struggling and need help is 
StackOverflow
.


